g');}@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) {#poseThumbNext2 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/seated_on_heels_prayer-tn@2x.png');}}</style><div id='poseThumbNext2'></div></a></li><li><a href='./Pose/seated_on_heels_twist_bound' title="Bound Revolved Squatting Toe Balance"><style>#poseThumbNext3 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/seated_on_heels_twist_bound_L-tn.png');}@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) {#poseThumbNext3 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/seated_on_heels_twist_bound_L-tn@2x.png');}}</style><div id='poseThumbNext3'></div></a></li></ul></section><section class='poseDescription'><ul><li><h3>Revolved Squatting Toe Balance</h3></li></ul><ul><li><h5 class='category'>Category:</h5><span class='cat'>Seated / Twist</span></li><li><h5 class='category'>Difficulty:</h5><span class='cat'>Intermediate</span></li></ul><ul><li><h5>Description:</h5><p class='text'>Start from <a href='./Pose/seated_on_heels_prayer'>Squatting Toe Balance</a> pose.  Slowly twist to one side, hooking the elbow to the outside of the opposite knee.  Gaze is towards the sky.  If possible, release the hands, lower hand wraps around the knees and the other hand around the back and try to bind the hands.</p></li></ul><ul><li><h5>Benefits:</h5><p class='text'>Strengthens arms, wrists and ankles.  Stretches the upper back.  Strengthens the abdominal muscles.</p></li></ul></section>        </section>

